Class SPOPredicate

    Direct Known Subclasses:
    AbstractRuleTestCase.P, SPOStarJoin, TestSPORelation.P

    public class SPOPredicate
extends Predicate<ISPO>
    A predicate that is a triple with one or more variables. While the general case allows a predicate to have an arbitrary name, for RDFS reasoning we are only concerned with predicates of the form triple(s,p,o).

    • Method Detail

      • clone

        public SPOPredicate clone()
        Description copied from class: Predicate
        Overridden to provide a fast path clone(). This avoids a constructor lookup via reflection in favor of simply creating a new Predicate instance. However, subclasses MUST override this method. This change was introduced on 11/17/2011 when a profiler showed a 13% of all time related to a join intensive process in CoreBaseBOp.clone() using reflection to make a copy of an Predicate.asBound(IBindingSet) predicate.
        Specified by:
        clone in interface BOp
        Overrides:
        clone in class Predicate<ISPO>

      • sid

        public final IVariable<IV> sid()
        The variable for the statement identifier (optional). The statement identifier is the composition of the (subject, predicate, and object) positions of the fully predicate. When this variable is declared, it will be bound to a SidIV for matched statements.
        See Also:
        SPOPredicate.Annotations.SID

      • asBound

        public SPOPredicate asBound(IBindingSet bindingSet)
        Strengthened return type.

        Fast path for as-bound.

        This reuses the annotations map since we know that the annotations will not be changed by Predicate.asBound(IBindingSet). That provides a significant reduction in heap churn.

        Specified by:
        asBound in interface IPredicate<ISPO>
        Overrides:
        asBound in class Predicate<ISPO>
        Parameters:
        bindingSet - The binding set.
        Returns:
        The as-bound IPredicate -or- null if the IPredicate can not be unified with the IBindingSet.
        See Also:
        (RDR query does too much work)
